Tales of the Legion of Super-Heroes #320
Publisher:  DC Comics
Publication Date:  February 1985

Writers:  Paul Levitz and Mindy Newell
Pencilers:  Dan Jurgens
Inker:  Karl Kesel
Colorist:  Carl Gafford
Letterer:  Adam Kubert
Cover:  Dan Jurgens, Karl Kesel, and Anthony Tollin

Story 1: Magpie Complex

A professional thief known as Magpie is hired by the mysterious Monitor and Harbinger, arms dealers, to steal an artifact from the headquarters of the Legion of Super-Heroes. The Legion is able to stop him before he steal anything but Magpie is still able to get away. The Monitor informs his client, Universo, of the failure but Universo informs Monitor that he has moved on to new plans to destroy the Legion. Meanwhile, other Legionnaires express their distrust of Computo.

Story 2: Triangle?

Sun Boy believes he sees Officer Gigi Cusimano and Colossal Boy together, believing they are having an affair. However, it was all a plot for Gigi to get some revenge against Sun Boy for hurting her in their relationship.

